      "content": "the pre-order thing is too slow to set up and the marketing team already spent the budget on the current \"in stock\" campaign. look, if we drop the listing now, our velocity score hits zero and the algorithm will bury us. can we just keep it as 'in stock' for the next few days? even if we have to manually delay some orders or scramble to find stock from other vendors later, we just can't afford to let the listing go dark right now. what do you think?",
